ts participate in tokkatsu, which means “special activities.” Examples include a morning greeting, being class leader for the day, class meetings and cleaning. Tokkatsu are done in addition to lessons on school subjects. With JICA’s support, tokkatsu are now spreading to the classrooms of Egypt. This basic component of Japa...nese-style education is intended to complete the balanced development of students’ physical, emotional and intellectual abilities. These activities familiar in Japanese elementary schools were a series of novel surprises for Egyptian training participants. The participants took notes on how best to popularize tokkatsu in Egypt and asked the teachers questions. They wrote wishes on strips of paper with the children and hung them on a bamboo tree as a part of Tanabata, a Japanese seasonal tradition. May all of their wishes come true. See MoreJapan International Cooperation Agency - JICA · July 23 at 1:00am · India: Three more sewerage treatment plants added to Bengaluru this year with JICA support covering 3.5 million people’s sewerage in total. https://www.jica.go.jp/…/eng…/office/topics/press170707.htmlThree more Sewerage Treatment Plants Added to Bengaluru This Year with JICA Support | India | Countries & Regions | JICAJapan International Cooperation Agency (JICA) provides technical cooperation and other forms of aid promoting economic and social development in developing countries and aims to advance international cooperation.jica.go.jpJapan International Cooperation Agency - JICA · July 21 at 1:00am · Celebrating 50 years of ASEAN: JICA receives Certificate of Appreciation from Indonesia for its years of cooperation in infrastructure On July 15, Certificate of Appreciation was given to JICA by the Hon. Basuki Hadimuljono, Minister of Public Works and Housing of Indonesia. JICA will continue to strengthen the bond of cooperation between Japan and Indonesia. #ASEAN50Japan International Cooperation Agency - JICA added 4 new photos. · July 20 at