 on the jacket and tried to do various chores which their wives normally manage. They experienced the hardship women go through during pregnancy! https://www.facebook.com/jicaghana/posts/709799259221395JICA Ghana added 2 new photos. · June 14 · SUCCESS STORY OF A JICA VOLUNTEER IN UPPER WEST REGION Husbands, have you ever imagined the hardship of your wife during pregnancy?  The JICA volunteer in Upper... West Region invited both mothers and their husbands to a lecture on the difficulties women go through during pregnancy. In order to have real demonstration of this, the volunteer made “pregnancy jacket” with used backpack, which people can experience the feeling of a pregnant woman and asked all husbands to try carrying such jackets and do the various house chores our rural women normally go through for them to appreciate the need to assist their wives during such periods.  This lecture actually yielded result with various testimonies from pregnant women within the Lambussie area attesting to the fact that now their husbands have been helping them do some heavy duties during the pregnancy periods. Currently there are 77 Japanesse Volunteers in Ghana serving in various sectors of the economy.  ….. SEE BELOW SOME PICTURES FROM THE LECTURES See MoreJapan International Cooperation Agency - JICA · July 15 at 1:00am · Guidelines JICA helped create will be key to the development efforts of Sierra Leone, which has endured a long civil war and an Ebola epidemic. JICA restarted its development work in the country in June, 2016, after the epidemic was brought under control. And 1 years, JICA presented to the president the “Local Council’s Development Operational Guidelines.” As for recovery from Ebola, the guidelines include restoration of the depressed rural economy and efforts to create a hygienic health system. By disseminating the guidelines to local councils throughout the country, JICA aims to create local communities that are resilient to the next disaster, even if it 