o lead the work of FAO Forestry by putting to use his experiences from the various stages of his career. See MoreJapan International Cooperation Agency - JICA added 3 new photos. · July 13 at 4:00am · A Comprehensive Development Plan Centered on People’s Happiness — News from Overseas Offices, JICA Bhutan Office The JICA project for the “Formulation of the Comprehensive Development Plan for Bhutan 2030” invited high level Bhutanese government officials comprising of 5 secretaries to attend the first technical meeting for the project in Japan from May 15th -25th, 2017. Through learning from the experience of Japan, this is the first time for Bhutan to develop a national com...prehensive development plan, and the first in the world that a comprehensive development plan centered on “People’s Happiness” is being formulated. It is based on the concept of Gross National Happiness in Bhutan. The steering committee members of the project had an opportunity to make a field visit to Izumo and Ama-cho. They said that they learnt a lot from the experience of these small towns in Japan - they have overcome the challenges of rural-urban migration, declining population, for they have built strategies to develop focused economic activities. See MoreJapan International Cooperation Agency - JICA shared JICA Bhutan Office's photo. · July 13 at 1:00am · Bhutan: Every time the new volunteers arrive in Bhutan, His Majesty King Jigme Khesar Namgyel Wangchuck kindly delivers the gifts of Gho and Kira (traditional clothes of Bhutan). We would like to express our gratitude to His Majesty the King for your continuous support! Volunteers shall contribute to the development of your country.JICA Bhutan Office · July 10 at 2:09am · The newly arrived volunteers express their deepest gratitude and appreciation to His Majesty the King for the gifts of Gho and Kira. They are overwhelmingly excited to wear the gho and kira for the first time in their lives.Japan International Cooperation Agency - JICA